Question: What type of cultural arts or entertainment opportunities would you like to see more of in Austin?

Response ID: resp_666
Response Text: I am a visual artist and have many friends who sell at markets and in galleries. I often hear how difficult it is to find studio spaces in Austin. Average rental cost is close to $1000 and it’s usually for a space around 300-500 square ft.  Could ACME support up and coming artists with studio or material stipends through annual grant applications? Back home in Ohio a Non Profit called the GCAC (Greatest Columbus Arts Council) would provide $1200 grants to over 200 emerging  artists annually. 

What if ACME facilitated more mural events. If you go to other cities many orgs will fund virtual or public mural events where artists are paid a stipend to make public artwork. I’ve seen it done traditionally and with 3d projected illustrations and animations.

